And you're still
finding the pieces?

828
00:41:16,595 --> 00:41:17,115
Yes.

829
00:41:17,315 --> 00:41:18,276
Lots.

830
00:41:18,516 --> 00:41:19,676
A buzzard.

831
00:41:20,356 --> 00:41:23,035
He's here all the time, you know.

832
00:41:23,036 --> 00:41:26,476
Keeps us company.

833
00:41:26,916 --> 00:41:28,515
How about that.

834
00:41:28,516 --> 00:41:31,957
We have them too.

835
00:41:34,277 --> 00:41:36,356
Would you say Mrs Harris,

836
00:41:36,357 --> 00:41:38,836
I'd like to know would you say,

837
00:41:38,837 --> 00:41:45,357
on balance have
you led a happy life?

838
00:41:45,358 --> 00:41:49,917
Well, I have to wait till
it's over and I'll work that out.

839
00:41:49,918 --> 00:41:54,278
You're a strange man, Mr Quinlan

840
00:41:55,758 --> 00:41:59,398
Do you believe in keeping
promises, Mr Quinlan?

841
00:41:59,399 --> 00:42:00,639
Yes.

842
00:42:01,919 --> 00:42:05,118
What about the promises you
make to the dead?

843
00:42:05,119 --> 00:42:06,438
Do they count?

844
00:42:06,439 --> 00:42:07,639
Even more.

845
00:42:07,879 --> 00:42:10,278
I think promises are stupid.

846
00:42:10,279 --> 00:42:11,239
Why?

847
00:42:12,480 --> 00:42:18,039
Well I promise my granny
I'll wash the dishes.

848
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:22,000
And I mean to, but I never do.

849
00:42:22,760 --> 00:42:27,200
You're never free of the promises
that you make, you know.

850
00:42:27,201 --> 00:42:32,281
Even if you break them,
you're never free of them.

851
00:43:36,926 --> 00:43:39,085
It's the German.
It's the bloody Germans!

852
00:43:39,086 --> 00:43:39,885
It's not the Germans, granny.

853
00:43:39,886 --> 00:43:41,965
We have to get out of the house!

854
00:43:41,966 --> 00:43:43,765
Contact, Pound Street,
one man down.

855
00:43:43,766 --> 00:43:44,726
Wait out.

856
00:43:47,087 --> 00:43:48,326
Are you all right?

857
00:43:48,327 --> 00:43:49,686
I'm so sorry!

858
00:43:49,687 --> 00:43:50,966
It's not usually like this here.

859
00:43:50,967 --> 00:43:52,526
Belfast is a great place really.

860
00:43:52,527 --> 00:43:53,966
Only we have to
get out of here right now.

861
00:43:53,967 --> 00:43:55,686
- Get out? Why? Another bomb?
- There'll be another bomb.

862
00:43:55,687 --> 00:43:59,087
There's always a second bomb.
We have to get out! Come on!

863
00:43:59,088 --> 00:43:59,648
Shit!

864
00:43:59,888 --> 00:44:02,767
No pulse, he's a goner!

865
00:44:02,768 --> 00:44:04,607
There's another fucking bomb!

866
00:44:04,608 --> 00:44:05,368
Shit!

867
00:44:05,608 --> 00:44:06,647
Clear the street!

868
00:44:06,648 --> 00:44:08,287
Get everyone out now!

869
00:44:08,288 --> 00:44:08,928
Leave him!

870
00:44:09,168 --> 00:44:09,807
We'll pick him up later.

871
00:44:09,808 --> 00:44:10,728
Sir.

872
00:44:11,168 --> 00:44:12,327
I'm so sorry.

873
00:44:12,328 --> 00:44:14,168
I really am.

874
00:44:14,169 --> 00:44:15,328
Come on, Mrs Harris.

875
00:44:15,329 --> 00:44:16,888
Granny,
don't be bothering with that.

876
00:44:16,889 --> 00:44:18,248
Granny, get out!

877
00:44:18,249 --> 00:44:18,689
Come on!

878
00:44:18,929 --> 00:44:21,368
Come on, Mrs Harris, quickly.

879
00:44:21,369 --> 00:44:21,849
Move!

880
00:44:22,089 --> 00:44:22,728
Clear the streets!

881
00:44:22,729 --> 00:44:23,408
There's another bomb!

882
00:44:23,409 --> 00:44:24,728
Move, move!

883
00:44:24,729 --> 00:44:25,169
Come on!

884
00:44:25,449 --> 00:44:27,889
Top of the street!

885
00:44:27,890 --> 00:44:29,289
You stupid bitch!

886
00:44:29,290 --> 00:44:30,929
Get out the back door!

887
00:44:30,930 --> 00:44:31,370
Go!

888
00:44:31,570 --> 00:44:33,090
Go!

889
00:44:36,970 --> 00:44:40,771
Do not return to your houses!

890
00:44:42,611 --> 00:44:44,490
Right, get that cover hose on.

891
00:44:44,491 --> 00:44:46,370
Get them behind the wall.

892
00:44:46,371 --> 00:44:47,371
Fergus.

893
00:44:47,771 --> 00:44:48,291
Fergus?

894
00:44:48,531 --> 00:44:49,610
Mr Quinlan.

895
00:44:49,611 --> 00:44:51,010
Haven't seen you for a while.

896
00:44:51,011 --> 00:44:52,410
I have friends down here.

897
00:44:52,411 --> 00:44:53,371
Anyone hurt?

898
00:44:53,372 --> 00:44:55,011
Only that poor squaddie.

899
00:44:55,012 --> 00:44:56,731
And they want us to go down there
and get him.

900
00:44:56,732 --> 00:44:59,291
And blow more of us to pieces.

901
00:44:59,292 --> 00:45:00,371
We need to clear this area.

902
00:45:00,372 --> 00:45:01,811
Take her in, would you?

903
00:45:01,812 --> 00:45:04,732
You're okay.

904
00:45:13,893 --> 00:45:19,774
- I know her. No, sir, She's my friend.
- You can't go back. No way.

905
00:45:21,574 --> 00:45:24,093
I told you before,
you can't go down there.

906
00:45:24,094 --> 00:45:25,533
Clear the area immediately!

907
00:45:25,534 --> 00:45:29,894
There's another bomb there!
Get out of this street

908
00:45:34,295 --> 00:45:35,695
Oh my God.

909
00:45:38,455 --> 00:45:42,375
Clear the area!

910
00:45:52,416 --> 00:45:53,816
Oh God.

911
00:46:02,977 --> 00:46:04,056
Get back here!

912
00:46:04,057 --> 00:46:05,656
What the hell are you doing?

913
00:46:05,657 --> 00:46:07,216
Leave me be.

914
00:46:07,217 --> 00:46:10,456
There's something
I have to tell her.

915
00:46:10,457 --> 00:46:11,537
Hold it!

916
00:46:11,737 --> 00:46:15,498
That's as far as you're going.

917
00:46:15,898 --> 00:46:18,377
This is Pound Street, sir,
but we can't get through.

918
00:46:18,378 --> 00:46:20,497
Oh, this is okay.

919
00:46:20,498 --> 00:46:21,337
Thanks. Back!

920
00:46:21,338 --> 00:46:22,098
Move back!

921
00:46:22,298 --> 00:46:26,058
Get body cover on!

922
00:46:29,499 --> 00:46:30,219
Oh God.

923
00:46:30,459 --> 00:46:33,818
Oh Holy God!

924
00:46:33,819 --> 00:46:35,019
Mr Thomas!

925
00:46:35,219 --> 00:46:37,098
Please don't do it!

926
00:46:37,099 --> 00:46:38,739
Mr Thomas!

927
00:46:39,659 --> 00:46:41,100
Mr Thomas!

928
00:46:41,780 --> 00:46:43,299
Come on, quick as you can.

929
00:46:43,300 --> 00:46:44,340
Jack?

930
00:46:44,700 --> 00:46:45,980
Jack Etty?

931
00:46:47,180 --> 00:46:49,779
It's Eleanor.

932
00:46:49,780 --> 00:46:52,019
Eleanor Reilly.

933
00:46:52,020 --> 00:46:54,260
Jesus Christ, Eleanor.

934
00:46:54,261 --> 00:46:56,340
You must be looking for
Teddy's girl.

935
00:46:56,341 --> 00:46:58,100
Yeah, Teddy's girl.

936
00:46:58,101 --> 00:47:01,100
She's over there,
but we've all been evacuated.

937
00:47:01,101 --> 00:47:02,140
There's been one bomb,

938
00:47:02,141 --> 00:47:06,301
and they're saying
there will be another.

939
00:47:08,102 --> 00:47:11,741
Mr Thomas please.

940
00:47:11,742 --> 00:47:15,182
You bloody little eejit!

941
00:47:16,462 --> 00:47:19,661
Get away from here!

942
00:47:19,662 --> 00:47:23,383
Are you trying to
get yourself killed?

943
00:47:24,623 --> 00:47:27,862
We knew he'd be up here somewhere.

944
00:47:27,863 --> 00:47:28,903
Yes.

945
00:47:29,423 --> 00:47:32,983
Thank you, Jimmy.

946
00:47:34,744 --> 00:47:35,543
I'm sorry, sir, no further.

947
00:47:35,544 --> 00:47:39,624
No, wait a second, please.

948
00:47:44,184 --> 00:47:46,143
Mrs Harris?

949
00:47:46,144 --> 00:47:48,464
Come slowly away, please.

950
00:47:48,465 --> 00:47:50,264
There's another bomb here.

951
00:47:50,265 --> 00:47:51,185
I know.

952
00:47:51,425 --> 00:47:54,904
You move away, this is none of
your concern, Mr Quinlan.

953
00:47:54,905 --> 00:47:57,104
Yes, it is.

954
00:47:57,105 --> 00:47:59,224
Yes, it bloody is.

955
00:47:59,225 --> 00:48:02,145
You might survive, you know that?

956
00:48:02,146 --> 00:48:04,345
Just with bits of you blown off.

957
00:48:04,346 --> 00:48:06,905
Arms, legs, eyes.

958
00:48:06,906 --> 00:48:09,665
I've seen it.

959
00:48:09,666 --> 00:48:10,905
Teddy wouldn't like that, now...

960
00:48:10,906 --> 00:48:11,506
No.

961
00:48:12,066 --> 00:48:14,946
Nice try, Mr Quinlan.

962
00:48:14,947 --> 00:48:16,666
You're a brave man.

963
00:48:16,667 --> 00:48:17,747
No.

964
00:48:17,907 --> 00:48:21,147
No, I am not.

965
00:48:21,627 --> 00:48:25,946
Do you think he looked like this
when he crashed?

966
00:48:25,947 --> 00:48:27,348
No

967
00:48:27,668 --> 00:48:31,308
He was alive.

968
00:48:34,868 --> 00:48:36,547
I was there.

969
00:48:36,548 --> 00:48:38,787
Help me, please.

970
00:48:38,788 --> 00:48:40,188
Help me!

971
00:48:40,509 --> 00:48:41,029
What?

972
00:48:41,269 --> 00:48:41,749
Help.

973
00:48:41,949 --> 00:48:45,189
Help me, please.

974
00:48:50,309 --> 00:48:53,428
Please, kid, take it.

975
00:48:53,429 --> 00:48:55,989
Take the ring.

976
00:48:55,990 --> 00:49:01,429
Promise me to tell her she's free.

977
00:49:01,430 --> 00:49:08,710
Teddy says make her own choice
Ethel Ann.

978
00:49:08,711 --> 00:49:11,190
Give her the ring.

979
00:49:11,191 --> 00:49:14,510
Promise me.

980
00:49:14,511 --> 00:49:15,991
I promise.

981
00:49:25,232 --> 00:49:26,991
I didn't take it.

982
00:49:26,992 --> 00:49:28,711
I should have found you.

983
00:49:28,712 --> 00:49:31,831
Told you what he said.

984
00:49:31,832 --> 00:49:34,472
I looked for it.

985
00:49:34,473 --> 00:49:36,552
All my life.

986
00:49:36,553 --> 00:49:38,433
The ring.

987
00:49:40,673 --> 00:49:44,513
You were free.

988
00:49:45,033 --> 00:49:49,634
He wanted me to tell you that.

989
00:49:49,674 --> 00:49:53,714
I'm so sorry.

990
00:50:21,036 --> 00:50:23,076
Goodbye.

991
00:50:28,197 --> 00:50:29,237
Ethel.

992
00:50:30,757 --> 00:50:32,357
Please!

993
00:50:32,557 --> 00:50:34,516
We have to go, Mrs Harris.

994
00:50:34,517 --> 00:50:36,596
Have to go now.

995
00:50:36,597 --> 00:50:38,157
Come on.

996
00:50:45,838 --> 00:50:49,158
No, no! No!

997
00:51:12,720 --> 00:51:14,759
Have you ever been in love,
Mr Quinlan?

998
00:51:14,760 --> 00:51:15,720
No.

999
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:18,639
Life is hard enough.

1000
00:51:18,640 --> 00:51:22,240
So, is it possible to
love more than once?

1001
00:51:22,241 --> 00:51:23,480
I know I have.

1002
00:51:23,481 --> 00:51:26,801
That's for sure.

1003
00:51:36,722 --> 00:51:38,441
We've left it a bit late.

1004
00:51:38,442 --> 00:51:39,961
Well, that was my fault.

1005
00:51:39,962 --> 00:51:42,281
According to Marie,
it was my fault.

1006
00:51:42,282 --> 00:51:44,081
I don't know why I should
get all the blame.

1007
00:51:44,082 --> 00:51:45,201
Because you're an easy target.

1008
00:51:45,202 --> 00:51:47,281
You're getting too old
and too fat.

1009
00:51:47,282 --> 00:51:49,442
How come none of that
ever happened to you?

1010
00:51:49,443 --> 00:51:50,162
It happened to me.

1011
00:51:50,163 --> 00:51:50,963
Look.

1012
00:51:51,163 --> 00:51:54,602
But, if you promise to love
one person and no-one else,

1013
00:51:54,603 --> 00:51:56,682
for ever and ever?

1014
00:51:56,683 --> 00:51:58,602
You can't make promises like that.

1015
00:51:58,603 --> 00:52:00,362
Oh yes, you can.

1016
00:52:00,363 --> 00:52:02,643
You can't keep it.

1017
00:52:02,644 --> 00:52:06,404
Well worth making it, though.

1018
00:52:15,645 --> 00:52:17,644
I'd love to fly.

1019
00:52:17,645 --> 00:52:19,764
I'll take you up some time.

1020
00:52:19,765 --> 00:52:21,364
Teddy was gonna take me flying.

1021
00:52:21,365 --> 00:52:22,644
He promised.

1022
00:52:22,645 --> 00:52:26,644
Teddy, Teddy, Teddy

1023
00:52:26,645 --> 00:52:30,805
He was the greatest guy
in the world when he was alive.

1024
00:52:30,806 --> 00:52:35,966
But once dead, my God,
what a pain in the ass!

1025
00:52:59,288 --> 00:53:03,328
What's happening to me?

1026
00:53:04,088 --> 00:53:08,408
You're grieving, girl.



